1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with transmission schemes and capacity over a block fading channel, which is a topic within information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the transmission of data over a channel, which is a fundamental aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes and compares different transmission schemes, which can be seen as control systems for the transmission process. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions an underlying application that requires a constant rate of message delivery, which could be related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - While not the main focus of the paper, the proposed transmission schemes involve encoding and decoding algorithms, which could be relevant to data structures and algorithms.
